            We were searching for a solution to write tests which are good to read and easy to write. It must be able to run on several browsers and understandable across different teams with different knowledge and different frameworks in usage. <strong>CodeceptJS helps us with all this and much more at Porsche</strong> and we are happy that we made that decision.
        </p>
        <div class="signature">
            <Image src={_mitko} alt=""/>
            <div class="text">
                <div class="title">
                    Mitko Tschimev
                </div>
                Frontend Tech Lead at <strong>My Porsche Core</strong>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<style lang="scss">
    .card-container {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
        grid-gap: 90px 60px;
        padding-top: 60px;
    }

    .card {
        box-shadow: rgba(100, 100, 111, 0.2) 0 7px 29px 0;
        border-radius: 2rem;
        padding: 30px;
        line-height: normal;
        background-color: #ffffff;
        position: relative;
        margin-top: 0 !important;

        svg {
            position: absolute;
            left: -16px;
            top: -16px;
            fill: var(--sl-color-text-accent);
            width: 36px;
            height: 36px;
            border-radius: 999rem;
            background-color: #ffffff;
        }
    }

    .signature {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;

        img {
            width: 60px;
            border-radius: 999rem;
            margin-right: 1rem;
        }
    }

    .text {
        margin-top: 0 !important;
    }

    .title {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
    }

</style>